    tag: 'hardening',
    body: 'Phase 3 prep (Week 9). Migration 0054 used to create the GIN index on usage_events.properties via the non-concurrent CREATE INDEX … USING GIN form, which holds an AccessExclusiveLock on usage_events for the whole index build (rolled into the 53.5s figure on 5M rows in docs/migration-safety-findings.md). CONCURRENTLY is the canonical fix, but it can\'t run inside a transaction block, and golang-migrate v4.19.1\'s postgres driver doesn\'t support a per-file x-no-tx-wrap flag (only the sqlite drivers do). The runner in internal/platform/migrate/migrate.go now detects an opt-out header — `-- velox:no-transaction` on its own line within the first 5 lines of a migration file — and applies those files via our own db.ExecContext with autocommit, after splitting on `;` so each statement runs separately. Migrations without the header keep running through golang-migrate exactly as before. The GIN index is now owned by the new 0062_usage_events_gin_concurrent migration with the header set; up uses CREATE INDEX CONCURRENTLY IF NOT EXISTS, down uses DROP INDEX CONCURRENTLY IF EXISTS, both no-tx. Re-running the safety harness shows 0062 with 0ms AccessExclusiveLock observed on usage_events.',
